{
  "id": "3FHS6Bqr",
  "slug": "cobbledloot-cobblemon",
  "title": "CobbledLoot [Cobblemon]",
  "description": "A more lightweight version of PokeLoot, featuring small loots that are scattered around the world that give you a reward!",
  "body": "<div align=\"center\">\n    <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/modpack/cobblemon-origins\" target=\"_blank\">\n      <img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/qOVttPN.png\" alt=\"\">\n    </a>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\n  <a href=\"https://discord.gg/Rhd62tkW9M\" target=\"_blank\">\n    <img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fKxX2Su.png\" alt=\"Discord\">\n  </a>\n</p>\n</div>\n\n---\n\n<h1>🔴 CobbledLoot ⚪</h1>\nThis datapack adds small Pokéballs around your world that when claimed, will give you a tiny reward!\n<br>\n<br>\nCobbledLoot is a fork of one of my favorite projects, <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/datapack/cobblemon-pokeloot\">PokeLoot</a>! I've decided to make a fork of this project, since I've found a new way to generate the PokeLoots, we all love, in a different way from before with server performance in mind. This should be way more lightweight and better for server performance. Unlike PokeLoot, CobbledLoot focuses on minimal performance impact, making it an excellent choice for large servers. It also supports loot generation in both newly generated and previously explored chunks. However, please note that this is not an update to PokeLoot, but a separate datapack that works differently.\n<br>\n<br>\n<strong> Important (⚠️) </strong>This datapack requires a resource pack to function properly. Make sure to place the ZIP file in both your resourcepacks and datapacks folders.\n<br>\n<br>\n<h2>✅ Pros of CobbledLoot ✅</h2>\n<ul>\n1. <strong>High performance</strong> – Designed to be significantly more lightweight, ideal for large multiplayer servers.\n<br>\n2. <strong>Universal chunk support</strong> – Loots generate in both old and new chunks, so it works in any world.\n<br>\n3. <strong>Plug-and-play</strong> – Easy to set up with no need for configuration.\n</ul>\n<h2>❌ Cons of CobbledLoot ❌</h2>\n<ul>\n1. <strong>Resource pack required</strong> – Won’t work without resourcepack.\n<br>\n2. <strong>Limited customization</strong> – Offers fewer configuration options compared to PokeLoot.\n<br>\n3. <strong>Challeging to integrate</strong> – Can be hard for players to integrate it into other resourcepacks/datapacks.\n</ul>\n<h2>🤔 Which one should you use? 🤔</h2>\n<ul>\nIf you're running a small server or playing solo, PokeLoot is a great choice thanks to its customization and it shouldn't impact your server performance. However, if you're running a larger server or if you are concerned about performance, CobbledLoot is a better fit.\n</ul>\n<h2>🥚 Spawning CobbledLoot commands 💥</h2> \n<ul>\n<li>You can use <ins>/function cobbledloot:give_pokeball_spawner</ins> to give yourself an armorstand. Place this armorstand anywhere in your world to spawn a pokeball loot.</li>\n<li>You can also use <ins>/function cobbledloot:give_greatball_spawner</ins> to give yourself an armorstand. Place this armorstand anywhere in your world to spawn a greatball loot.</li>\n<li>You can also use <ins>/function cobbledloot:give_ultraball_spawner</ins> to give yourself an armorstand. Place this armorstand anywhere in your world to spawn a ultraball loot.</li>\n<li>You can also use <ins>/function cobbledloot:give_masterball_spawner</ins> to give yourself an armorstand. Place this armorstand anywhere in your world to spawn a masterball loot.</li>\n<li>You can also use <ins>/function pokeloot:kill_pokeloots</ins> to kill all pokeloots.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>📋 CobbledLoot List 📋</h2>\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Pokeball:</strong> <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/6/6f/Poke_Ball.png\"> Poke Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/1/10/Dive_Ball.png\"> Dive Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/5/50/Dusk_Ball.png\"> Dusk Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/f/f8/Fast_Ball.png\"> Fast Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/3/30/Friend_Ball.png\"> Friend Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/4/45/Great_Ball.png\"> Great Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/2/24/Heal_Ball.png\"> Heal Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/1/13/Heavy_Ball.png\"> Heavy Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/5/5b/Level_Ball.png\"> Level Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/0/0d/Love_Ball.png\"> Love Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/0/0a/Lure_Ball.png\"> Lure Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/8/8d/Luxury_Ball.png\"> Luxury Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/b/b0/Moon_Ball.png\"> Moon Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/a/a6/Nest_Ball.png\"> Nest Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/b/bb/Net_Ball.png\"> Net Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/8/8d/Premier_Ball.png\"> Premier Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/b/be/Quick_Ball.png\"> Quick Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/7/75/Repeat_Ball.png\"> Repeat Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/4/46/Safari_Ball.png\"> Safari Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/7/7d/Sport_Ball.png\"> Sport Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/4/46/Timer_Ball.png\"> Timer Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/3/34/Ultra_Ball.png\"> Ultra Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/7/71/Antidote.png\"> Antidote; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/b/b7/Awakening.png\"> Awakening; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/1/10/Burn_Heal.png\"> Burn Heal; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/8/8b/Dire_Hit.png\"> Dire hit; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/4/43/Elixir.png\"> Elixir; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/1/14/Energy_Root.png\"> Energy Root; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/3/3c/Ether.png\"> Ether; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/9/9c/Full_Heal.png\"> Full Heal; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/c/c3/Full_Restore.png\"> Full Restore; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/0/01/Guard_Spec.png\"> Guard Spec; <img src=\"https://wi