oice_Scarf.png\"> Choice Scarf; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/e/eb/Choice_Specs.png\"> Choice Specs; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/8/8d/Destiny_Knot.png\"> Destiny Knot; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/b/b8/Heavy-Duty_Boots.png\"> Heavy Duty Boots; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/7/7f/Leftovers.png\"> Leftovers; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/7/72/Lucky_Egg.png\"> Lucky Egg; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/c/c7/Muscle_Band.png\"> Muscle Band; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/3/39/Power_Anklet.png\"> Power Anklet; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/d/d7/Power_Band.png\"> Power Band; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/a/a3/Power_Belt.png\"> Power Belt; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/5/5b/Power_Bracer.png\"> Power Bracer; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/c/c4/Power_Lens.png\"> Power Lens; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/d/d9/Power_Weight.png\"> Power Weight; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/f/f7/Rocky_Helmet.png\"> Rocky Helmet; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/d/da/Wise_Glasses.png\"> Wise Glasses; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/f/f5/Exp._Share.png\"> Exp Share; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/f/f4/Exp._Candy_XS.png\"> Exp Candy XS; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/8/88/Exp._Candy_S.png\"> Exp Candy S; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/4/4d/Exp._Candy_M.png\"> Exp Candy M; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/a/ad/Exp._Candy_L.png\"> Exp Candy L; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/c/c6/Exp._Candy_XL.png\"> Exp Candy XL; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/a/a2/Rare_Candy.png\"> Rare Candy; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/5/59/Dubious_Disc.png\"> Dubious Disc; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/0/0c/Galarica_Cuff.png\"> Galarica Cuff; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/8/86/Galarica_Wreath.png\"> Galarica Wreath; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/3/33/Link_Cable.png\"> Link Cable; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/1/19/Blunder_Policy.png\"> Blunder Policy; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/e/e0/Eviolite.png\"> Eviolite; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/c/c7/Expert_Belt.png\"> Expert Belt; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/4/49/Focus_Sash.png\"> Focus Sash; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/a/a5/Life_Orb.png\"> Life Orb; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/4/45/Weakness_Policy.png\"> Weakness Policy; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/9/90/Ability_Capsule.png\"> Ability Capsule; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/2/2b/Ability_Patch.png\"> Ability Patch; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/f/f9/Beast_Ball.png\"> Beast Ball; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/2/23/Safety_Goggles.png\"> Safety Goggles; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/1/17/Room_Service.png\"> Room Service; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/a/a9/Terrain_Extender.png\"> Terrain Extender; <img src=\"https://wiki.cobblemon.com/images/0/03/Throat_Spray.png\"> Throat Spray;\n</li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<h2>📝 Change CobbledLoot List 📝</h2>\n<ul>\n<strong>Important Note: </strong>Modifying datapacks can be challenging for beginners. Proceed with caution! <strong> ⚠️ </strong><br>\n<br>\nTo customize the items found in each loot, you'll need to have the datapack folder unzipped and placed in your datapacks directory. Once unzipped, navigate to the following location: <pre>CobbledLootDatapack\\data\\cobbledloot\\loot_table</pre> In this folder, you'll find JSON files for each type of loot, such as pokeballs, ultraballs, greatballs, and masterballs. These files contain the items they correspond to.\n\nTo change an item, open the .json file of the loot you'd like to change and locate an item which will look like this: <ins>\"name\": \"cobblemon:poke_ball\".</ins> For example, if you want to replace the pokeball drop with a rare candy, change <ins>\"name\": \"cobblemon:poke_ball\"</ins> to <ins>\"name\": \"cobblemon:rare_candy\".</ins>\n\nYou can find the namespaces for cobblemon items by pressing F3+H in-game and hovering your mouse over an item.\n\nTo remove items, simply delete the corresponding section:\n<pre>\n{\n    \"type\": \"item\",\n    \"weight\": 1,\n    \"name\": \"cobblemon:poke_ball\"\n}\n</pre>\nTo add more items, simply add a new section:\n<pre>\n{\n    \"type\": \"item\",\n    \"weight\": 1,\n    \"name\": \"cobblemon:poke_ball\"\n}\n</pre>\nRemember to add a comma \",\" after each item (except the last one). Essentially, it's a JSON list separated by commas. If you've modified any of these .json files and the cobbledloots stop working, you might have misspelled an item in the namespace or used an item that doesn't exist in Minecraft's namespace. Additionally, double-check that your .json file is properly formatted by using an online JSON formatter.\n<br>\n</ul>\n<h2>🐣 Change CobbledLoot Spawn Rates 🐣</h2>\n<ul>\nTo change the Loots spawn rates, navigate to the following location: <pre>CobbledLootDatapack\\data\\cobblemon\\spawn_pool_world\\npcs</pre> In this folder, you'll find JSON files for each type of loot, such as pokeballs, ultraballs, greatballs, and masterballs. These files contain the spawning for each loot.\n\nTo change the chance of one spawning simply change the <ins>\"weight\"</ins> value. You can also change the <ins>\"bucket\"</ins> of a certain loot. There are 4 types of buckets: <ins>common</ins>, <ins>uncommon</ins>, <ins>rare</ins> and <ins>ultra-rare</ins>. If you want to make a loot rarer it's probably easier to change the <ins>\"bucket\"</ins> of that loot.\n\n<strong>Important (⚠️) </strong>If you want to use this datapack on your Server contact me first.\n<br>\n<br>\nBig thanks to @instrafe that gave me the idea to remake the datapack in this unique way!\n<br>\n<br>\nHave some issues? You can join the Official Cobblemon discord server, search for 'CobbledLoot' and ask your questions there, or alternatively, you can DM me on discord.\n<br>\n<br>\n<div style=\"width: 150px; text-align: center; margin-bottom: -10px;\">\n    <img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/BWJysFv.png\" alt=\"Image on the left\" style=\"float: left;\">\n    <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/user/Quim201\" target=\"_blank\">\n        <img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/uNv8h0k_d.png?maxwidth=320&shape=thumb&fidelity=high\" alt=\"Image that links to a user profile\" style=\"float: right;\">\n    </a>\n</div>\n<br>\n</ul>",
